this is some heavy artillery going on here :)
Generally speaking FunctionFactory instances are singletons already, this could perhaps remove static variable use. Then double-check locking can perhaps be replaced with
if (instance == null) {
    instance = new Memoizer(message(configuration));
}
The worst case scenario is that under very heavy load we might have several classes created unnecessarily. But realistically this is very small and unlikely overhead in the name of code simplicity.

